  "forecast_text": "PHZ112-121430-\nKauai Leeward Waters-\n316 PM HST Sat Jul 11 2026\n\n...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT THROUGH SUNDAY AFTERNOON...\n\n.TONIGHT...East northeast winds 20 to 25 knots. Seas 6 to 8 feet.\nWave Detail: East 7 feet at 7 seconds and southwest 3 feet at\n16 seconds. Isolated showers. \n.SUNDAY...East northeast winds 15 to 20 knots. Seas 5 to 7 feet.\nWave Detail: East 6 feet at 7 seconds and southwest 3 feet at\n16 seconds. Isolated showers in the morning, then scattered\nshowers in the afternoon. \n.SUNDAY NIGHT...East northeast winds 20 to 25 knots, easing to\n15 to 20 knots after midnight. Seas 5 to 7 feet. Wave Detail:\nEast 6 feet at 7 seconds and southwest 3 feet at 15 seconds.\nScattered showers, mainly in the evening. \n.MONDAY...East northeast winds 15 to 20 knots. Seas 5 to 7 feet.\nWave Detail: East 6 feet at 7 seconds and southwest 3 feet at\n15 seconds. Isolated showers. \n.MONDAY NIGHT...East northeast winds 15 to 20 knots. In the\nKaulakahi Channel, east northeast winds 10 to 15 knots, becoming\n7 to 10 knots after midnight. Seas 5 to 7 feet. Wave Detail: East\n5 feet at 6 seconds and southwest 3 feet at 14 seconds. Isolated\nshowers. \n.TUESDAY...East northeast winds to 15 knots...East northeast\n10 to 15 knots in the Kaulakahi Channel. Seas 4 to 6 feet. Wave\nDetail: East 5 feet at 6 seconds. Scattered showers, mainly in\nthe morning. \n.TUESDAY NIGHT...East winds 15 to 20 knots. Seas 4 to 6 feet.\nWave Detail: East 4 feet at 6 seconds. Scattered showers. \n.WEDNESDAY...East winds 10 to 15 knots. Seas 4 to 6 feet. Wave\nDetail: East northeast 4 feet at 6 seconds. Scattered showers in\nthe morning, then isolated showers in the afternoon. Scattered\nshowers through the day. \n.THURSDAY...East winds 10 to 15 knots, rising to 15 to 20 knots.\nSeas 4 to 5 feet. Wave Detail: East 5 feet at 6 seconds.\nScattered showers."
